gomodel:SYNGO_1773  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.7C,D shows that Farp1 regulates postsynaptic Rac1 using an optical probe for Rac1 activity, with knockdown of Farp1 reducing Rac1 activity and overexpression of Farp1 increasing it.\nFarp1 promotes steady-state spine F-actin amounts as shown in Fig.8A,B,D and F-actin assembly in spines as shown in Fig. 8C,D.. Experimental description: 1/11/2017 Pim\n- Cells: \"Primary hippocampal neurons were dissected at P0 from rats or SynCAM 1 KO mice\"\n- Cells in Fig.7 are rat (panel A/D).\n- Cells in Fig.8 are rat." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1773" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

